<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1265514" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=500%2C281&#038;ssl=1" alt=" Court rewards INEC staffs with imprisonment for receiving bribes" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Two of the members of staff of Independent National Electoral Commission have been sentenced to 42 years imprisonment by a high court in Yola presided by Justice Nathan Musa for receiving a bribe. Justice Musa asked that Diezani Allison Madueke, former Minister for Petroleum be produced by Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, and the International Police to face the court over  N362 million she sent to the two convicted INEC staff in order to compromise the 2015 presidential election in Adamawa State. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC had brought the case against Ibrahim Mohammed Umar, Sahabo Iya Hamman, both staff of INEC as well as the former Minister of Petroleum for conspiring to defraud the federal government with the intent to compromise the 2015 general elections. Musa said the court delivered the verdict after due diligence established a conspiracy between the persons, as such he convicted and sentenced the two INEC staff to seven years each on the three counts brought against them by the EFCC. The judge said he was giving a lenient sentence since the accused were first-term offenders adding that the sentence would run concurrently. “The offense has a mandatory provision. I’m constrained by the law. They shall be sentenced to seven years imprisonment without the option of fine. ” However in view of plea to temper justice with mercy, I will allow the sentence to run concurrently,” he said. vanguard Mr Christian Nwosu, ex-Administrative Secretary of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), has been sentenced for accepting bribe offered by former petroleum minister Diezani Alison-Madueke, to compromise the 2015 elections. January 24, 2019 In "News" The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC on Monday  arraigned three officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, at the Federal High Court sitting in Lagos and charged them with receiving N179.8 million  stolen money as bribe  from former oil minister, Diezani Alison-Madueke. July 30, 2018 In "News" The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) says it has written the presidency for further action on six of its former personnel involved in the N23 billion election bribe doled out by Diezani Alison-Madueke, former petroleum minister. April 12, 2017 In "News"